# Word To Markdown Specs

When working on the `specs/` Word-to-Markdown conversion files, use the personal skill `word-to-markdown-visual`.

Follow these constraints:
- Treat MS Word visual layout as the source of truth.
- Treat Cursor Preview as the target renderer.
- Do not declare the output fixed just because DOCX metadata or structural validation passes.
- Validate section by section, then inspect the generated Markdown/HTML only after a visual mismatch is identified.
- Prefer stable HTML over pure Markdown when Cursor Preview misrenders numbering, indentation, tables, or boxed blocks.
- For numbered descendants such as `3.1`, `4.5.1`, or `1.1.1`, avoid containers that Preview can render with stray bullets.
